Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.85,0:00:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have been investigating the murder of Professor Odagiri from one year ago.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.73,0:00:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you keep the voltage at max and wear it for more than five minutes...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.40,0:00:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,...then it will be lethal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.70,0:00:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kusakabe is not here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.87,0:00:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He isn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.04,0:00:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}His computer is not at his desk and \Nwe haven't been able to contact him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.96,0:00:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it. The truth behind the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.34,0:00:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is the murderer the Professor's assistant, Kasai Hitomi...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.63,0:00:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...the imprisoned convict Nishihori Kouya...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.13,0:00:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...or the isolated Public Safety officer, Kusakabe Akira?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.22,0:00:41.14,Default Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or perhaps...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.14,0:00:44.45,EpTitle,,0,0,0,,{\fad(398,478)\an1\move(1189,620,350,585,23,397)\fs42}{\c&H5B42D3&\3c&HDAE3E6&}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWhy{\c\3c\be1} was Professor Banno \NEpisode 4 \h\hplanning the Global Freeze?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.14,0:00:44.14,Default Top,,0,0,0,,Just who is the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.56,0:00:47.56,Default Top,,0,0,0,,Kaisai, Nishihori or Kusakabe?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.27,0:00:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The culprit is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.35,0:00:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,...none of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.45,0:00:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.66,0:00:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the night before the Professor died.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.76,0:01:01.90,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(485,0)\4a00\fs56\shad3\bord1.6\pos(640,570)\3c&H010100&}April 7th, 2014 (Monday)  9:32 PM
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.99,0:01:04.49,Default Top,,0,0,0,,Irritated with the Professor, Nishihori increased the voltage of the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.12,0:01:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And the day of the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.45,0:01:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,...as revenge for plagiarizing her work...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.03,0:01:14.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(475,480)\4a00\fs56\shad3\bord1.6\pos(640,570)\3c&H010100&}April 8th, 2014 (Tuesday)  6:05 PM
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.30,0:01:15.85,Default Top,,0,0,0,,...Kasai put a medicine that would place an intense strain on the Professor's heart into his cup,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.40,0:01:17.70,Default Top,,0,0,0,,with the intent of murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.75,0:01:20.16,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(475,0)\4a00\fs56\shad3\bord1.6\pos(640,570)\3c&H010100&}April 8th, 2014 (Tuesday)  6:48 PM
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.22,0:01:23.72,Default Top,,0,0,0,,But Kyu spilled the contents of that cup, and so it has no relevance to the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.83,0:01:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Professor!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.56,0:01:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So then the cause of the Professor's death must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.52,0:01:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Nishihori raising the voltage on the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.05,0:01:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But you won't die unless you wear it for over 5 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.78,0:01:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I see! The Professor died on the night of the Global Freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.37,0:01:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it, Gou. You're pretty sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.08,0:01:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.91,0:01:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Put simply, the moment the Professor put on the helmet...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.17,0:01:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Global Freeze happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.48,0:02:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it break?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.36,0:02:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.07,0:02:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.83,0:02:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't move my body!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.05,0:03:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is no murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.67,0:03:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.88,0:03:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But isn't the culprit still Nishihori?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.60,0:03:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of him raising the \Nvoltage that the Professor died.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.64,0:03:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Nishihori couldn't have predicted the Global Freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.31,0:03:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He never deliberately attempted to kill the Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.07,0:03:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.41,0:03:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Gou?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.99,0:03:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There is still something I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.70,0:03:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You felt it as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. What Kyu said before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.17,0:03:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He said that he used to run into Banno a lot during his walks.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.84,0:04:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They even met after he died, apparently.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.14,0:04:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If this case was an accident, does that mean Banno is unrelated?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.52,0:04:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.98,0:04:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The name Banno was written in the Professor's planner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.06,0:04:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,, The Anima System's data was not found on the Professor's computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.65,0:04:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if his death was an accident...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.10,0:04:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,...someone did wipe the data from his computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.40,0:04:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,An accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.47,0:04:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So why was I working so hard to find a murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.77,0:04:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But the case is not over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.70,0:04:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.57,0:05:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's from Kyu.
